'''Lauren Danielle Drain''' (born December 31, 1985) is an American [[nurse]] and author known for writing the 2013 book ''Banished'', which chronicles her experiences and eventual banishment from the controversial [[Westboro Baptist Church]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.goodreads.com/book/show/15791137-banished|title=Banished: Surviving My Years in the Westboro Baptist Church by Lauren Drain - Reviews, Discussion, Bookclubs, Lists|publisher=Goodreads.com|accessdate=2013-04-18}}</ref>

==Early life==
Drain was born in [[Tampa, Florida]] and lived in nearby [[Bradenton, Florida|Bradenton]] until age five, when she moved to [[Olathe, Kansas]] as her father, Steve, enrolled in a graduate program at the [[University of Kansas]].<ref>''Banished, [http://books.google.com/books?id=RSTUo3EUj8wC&pg=PT151&dq=%22lauren+drain%22+tampa&hl=en&sa=X&ei=gsv-UfChHdHwigKdl4AI&ved=0CEgQ6AEwAA#v=snippet&q=tampa&f=false first page in chapter 1] and [http://books.google.com/books?id=RSTUo3EUj8wC&pg=PT151&dq=%22lauren+drain%22+tampa&hl=en&sa=X&ei=gsv-UfChHdHwigKdl4AI&ved=0CEgQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=bradenton&f=false another page]: "Mom and Dad found us a house to rent in Bradenton"</ref>

Steve Drain first came into contact with Westboro while working on a documentary critical of the church.  He eventually became a fervent convert, and his entire family followed him into the church.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2013/03/05/banished-lauren-drain-on-growing-up-in-the-westboro-baptist-church.html|title=<U+2018>Banished<U+2019> Lauren Drain on Growing Up in the Westboro Baptist Church|last=Sessions|first=David|publisher=[[The Daily Beast]]|date=2013-03-05}}</ref>  Lauren Drain was a member from 2001 until 2008, when she was excommunicated for questioning church doctrine.<ref name="Advocate"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.laurendrain.com/about.html|title=Lauren Drain|publisher=Lauren Drain|accessdate=2013-04-18}}</ref> Her parents, two sisters, and brother are still members of the church, and have cut all ties with her.<ref name="60 Minutes">{{cite web|last=Hayes|first=Liz|title=Pure Hate|url=http://sixtyminutes.ninemsn.com/stories/8251593/pure-hate|work=ninemsn|publisher=60 Minutes|accessdate=30 May 2013}}</ref>

Drain graduated from Topeka West High School in [[Topeka, Kansas]] and earned a Wiseman Scholarship to [[Washburn University]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Washburn 2003-04 scholarship winners|url=http://cjonline.com/stories/031203/was_scholwinners.shtml|work=Topeka Capital-Journal|accessdate=August 4, 2013|date=March 12, 2003}}</ref>

==Career==
Drain graduated from [[Washburn University]] in 2007 with a [[Bachelor of Science in Nursing|Bachelor of Science degree in nursing]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Class of 2007: Washburn University|url=http://cjonline.com/stories/031203/was_scholwinners.shtml|work=Topeka Capital-Journal|accessdate=August 4, 2013|date=May 21, 2007}}</ref> Drain has been married to David Kagan since August 2013 and lives in [[New Britain, Connecticut]]. She currently works as a [[Cardiac nursing|cardiac nurse]].<ref name="Advocate">{{cite web|last=Brydum|first=Sunnivie|url=http://www.advocate.com/politics/religion/2013/03/14/escaping-westboro-former-church-member-lauren-drain-reveals-what-made|title=Escaping Westboro: Former Church Member Lauren Drain Reveals What Made Her Change|publisher=Advocate.com|date=2013-03-14|accessdate=2013-04-18}}</ref><ref name="LJ World">{{cite web|url=http://www2.ljworld.com/news/2013/mar/18/book-review-banished-phelps/|title=Book review: Banished by Phelps|author=Kraus, Susan|work=Lawrence Journal-World|date=March 18, 2013|accessdate=August 4, 2013}}</ref>

Drain joined [[NOH8 Campaign]] in 2013.<ref>{{cite news|last=Sieczkowski|first=Cavan|title=Lauren Drain, Former Westboro Baptist Church Member, Poses For NOH8 Campaign|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/02/11/lauren-drain-westboro-baptist-church-noh8-campaign-photo_n_2663854.html|accessdate=13 July 2013|newspaper=The Huffington Post|date=11 February 2013}}</ref>

Drain wrote a book titled ''Banished: Surviving My Years in the Westboro Baptist Church'', which describes her experiences in the Westboro Baptist Church and her ultimate expulsion from the church.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amazon.ca/Banished-Surviving-Westboro-Baptist-ebook/dp/B008TU2LS2|title=Banished: Surviving My Years in the Westboro Baptist Church eBook: Lauren Drain, Lisa Pulitzer: Amazon.ca: Kindle Store|publisher=Amazon.ca|accessdate=2013-04-18}}</ref> It has been on the [[New York Best Sellers list]] in the eBook category as of March 30, 2013.<ref>{{cite web|last=Cowles|first=Gregory |url=http://www.nytimes.com/best-sellers-books/e-book-nonfiction/list.html|title=Best Sellers - The New York Times|publisher=Nytimes.com|accessdate=2013-04-18}}</ref>

